Package com.peyrona.mingle.lang.japi

Class Logger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.peyrona.mingle.lang.japi.Logger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILogger
    public final class Logger
extends java.lang.Object
implements ILogger
    This class allows to easily work with logging tasks in applications.

    Where are log files stored?
    If the System property "logs.dir" is defined, then it will be used, otherwise it will be: File( Config.getHomeDir(), "logs" ).

    If passed file name is empty, then exceptions are not stored into a file, they are only shown in System:out. Created by peyrona on 21/07/2013.
